

---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Operational Concepts"
  description="Core operating concepts used in the Wychwood operating architecture including operational context layers, company operating systems, and execution architecture."
>

<main>

  <section class="shell section-sm">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">

      <h1>Operational Concepts</h1>

      <p class="mt-6 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
        Scaling companies rarely fail because of strategy. They fail because the
        systems that convert strategy into execution break as complexity grows.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
        The concepts below describe the core operating architecture used to restore
        clarity, discipline, and predictable execution inside scaling organizations.
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>


  <section class="border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))]">
    <div class="shell section-sm">

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">

        <a href="/concepts/operational-context-layer" class="card p-6 block">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Operational Context Layer</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            The structured definition of entities, metrics, ownership, and decision
            rules that creates shared operational meaning across systems and teams.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/concepts/company-operating-system/" class="card p-6 block">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Company Operating System</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            The metrics, ownership structures, and execution routines that define
            how a company actually operates as it scales.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/concepts/execution-architecture/" class="card p-6 block">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Execution Architecture</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            The operating structure that connects strategy, operations, forecasting,
            and leadership cadence into a coherent execution system.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/concepts/decision-governance/" class="card p-6 block">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Decision Governance</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            The explicit ownership and escalation structure that ensures decisions
            are made consistently and efficiently.
          </p>
        </a>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</main>

</BaseLayout>